  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Procurement of vaccines for measles outbreak response in 14 health zones in Kasai, Kasai Central, Kasai Oriental, Kwilu, Maindombe and South Kivu Provinces</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">At the end of week 31, 171 Health Zones (33% of the total) are in epidemic. The number of cases reported in 2019 represents the highest peak reported annually by the country since 2010. 
The epidemic was declared on June 10, 2019 by the Ministry of Public Health. The epidemic is not controlled yet, and the risk of spread remains very high.
This project is aimed primarily at strengthening the medical care of patients with measles, contributing to the interruption of the chain of transmission and thereby help reduce the risk of resurgence of the epidemic in 14 priority areas in 6 Provinces. Kasai (Ndjoko-Punda), Kasai Central (Mwatshi, Katende), Kasai Oriental (Bibanga, Bipemba, Cilundu, Diulu, Lukelenge, Miabi, Nzaba and Tshishimbi), Kwilu (Bagata), Maindombe (Oshwe), South Kivu (Nyangezi)</narrative>
  </description>
